node.text:
Just read about this on 6Buzz and it made me sick. Kiska pictured above is the only killer whale held in captivity in Canada. She was captured from her family over 40 years ago near Iceland and held in a tiny pool at Marineland located in Niagara Falls, Ontario Canada. In the wild orcas swim 100+ miles a day and are highly social animals that stay with their pod (family) their entire lives. Kiska is held alone in a concrete pool where she swims around in circles and cries out looking for other whales. She was also used for breeding at Marine Land and watched all 5 of her calves die. Dr Naomi Rose a marine mammal scientist said that Kiska is "the worlds loneliest orca." 

If you want to help out please share the hashtag #freekiska or visit www.savesmooshi.com ❤️

node.text: Banksy's "Dismaland" exhibition full of powerful messages in Somerset, England -2015 👀 The Cinderella sculpture was titled "What it's like to be a real princess". After the exhibition closed, the building material for the project was repurposed as shelters for refugees in the Calais Jungle.
